00:26:02,311 --> 00:26:03,388
He told us about Jason.

515
00:26:04,513 --> 00:26:06,930
Oh, well, thank you, Dr. Hunt.

516
00:26:06,999 --> 00:26:08,515
It's gonna be great for him.

517
00:26:08,583 --> 00:26:09,983
Well, good luck.

518
00:26:13,756 --> 00:26:15,088
What?

519
00:26:15,157 --> 00:26:17,057
That was a really nice
thing you did for them.

520
00:26:17,142 --> 00:26:18,742
Well,

521
00:26:18,811 --> 00:26:22,512
I'm a really nice guy,
or so I've been told.

522
00:26:22,581 --> 00:26:24,492
<i>I would never ask you for that.</i>

523
00:26:24,516 --> 00:26:26,249
You're not asking.
I am telling you.

524
00:26:26,318 --> 00:26:28,485
Well...

525
00:26:28,553 --> 00:26:30,386
I don't believe you.

526
00:26:30,455 --> 00:26:33,190
Cristina, people change.

527
00:26:33,258 --> 00:26:35,926
I mean, you're not the same
person that you were when we met.

528
00:26:35,995 --> 00:26:37,194
I can change, too.

529
00:26:37,262 --> 00:26:39,697
Really?

530
00:26:39,765 --> 00:26:44,101
People who want kids
don't just stop wanting them.

531
00:26:46,872 --> 00:26:48,238
Don't give up things for me.

532
00:26:48,307 --> 00:26:51,274
Hey, I'm not.

533
00:26:51,343 --> 00:26:53,010
I haven't.

534
00:26:55,481 --> 00:26:57,481
I'm not giving up anything.

535
00:27:03,805 --> 00:27:05,600
Good.

536
00:27:05,624 --> 00:27:07,591
Good. Good.

537
00:27:07,659 --> 00:27:09,392
Yeah, slowly but surely.

538
00:27:09,461 --> 00:27:11,728
Just focus on your balance.

539
00:27:13,616 --> 00:27:17,067
How does it feel,
Jase, to walk again?

540
00:27:17,136 --> 00:27:20,620
It's pretty good.

541
00:27:20,689 --> 00:27:22,409
Yeah, I think he
needs to concentrate.

542
00:27:25,628 --> 00:27:28,195
It's amazing, in
just a few years.

543
00:27:28,263 --> 00:27:30,113
Unbelievable.

544
00:27:30,182 --> 00:27:32,427
Is Dr. Yang busy? I would
love for her to see this.

545
00:27:32,451 --> 00:27:34,018
Let me check, okay?

546
00:27:34,086 --> 00:27:35,936
Jason, are you all right?

547
00:27:36,889 --> 00:27:38,649
Jason!

548
00:27:39,591 --> 00:27:40,631
Get a crash cart!

549
00:27:40,659 --> 00:27:41,725
Jason?

550
00:27:46,782 --> 00:27:47,931
I need you.

551
00:27:48,684 --> 00:27:49,850
Yes.

552
00:27:49,919 --> 00:27:51,284
No. I can't.

553
00:27:51,353 --> 00:27:53,598
These abstracts were
supposed to go out an hour ago.

554
00:27:53,622 --> 00:27:55,233
You know what? Okay.
On-call room, but fast?

555
00:27:55,257 --> 00:27:57,457
No, no, it's not...
It's Jason Castor.

556
00:27:57,525 --> 00:27:59,054
He just had an
accident in the BCI lab.

557
00:27:59,078 --> 00:28:01,261
He has rhabdo, renal failure.

558
00:28:01,330 --> 00:28:05,982
Grey is putting a shunt in him,
but his wife's asking for you.

559
00:28:06,051 --> 00:28:08,935
Jason Castor, your
patient, the quadriplegic?

560
00:28:09,004 --> 00:28:10,904
We put him into
Derek and Callie's trial.

561
00:28:10,973 --> 00:28:12,205
His wife is...

562
00:28:12,274 --> 00:28:13,451
Right, right, right. Yes.

563
00:28:13,475 --> 00:28:15,025
Does he need a heart consult?

564
00:28:15,094 --> 00:28:17,561
No, no. She's just scared,
and she trusts you...

565
00:28:17,630 --> 00:28:19,763
You know, Owen,
I have to finish this.

566
00:28:19,832 --> 00:28:21,114
I've got seven prints going.

567
00:28:21,183 --> 00:28:22,449
Where's Ross?

568
00:28:22,518 --> 00:28:23,758
Ross can't do this.

569
00:28:23,802 --> 00:28:26,086
I'm one step away from
funding for animal trials.

570
00:28:28,657 --> 00:28:30,535
Owen, he's not my
patient anymore.

571
00:28:30,559 --> 00:28:31,958
If the guy's heart is fine,

572
00:28:32,027 --> 00:28:34,507
I don't have time to hold
someone's hand right now.

573
00:28:39,368 --> 00:28:41,768
You know what? You
saved her husband's life.

574
00:28:41,837 --> 00:28:43,447
You were the first
doctor she met.

575
00:28:43,471 --> 00:28:45,550
She likes you, she trusts you,
and now she's waiting for you.

576
00:28:45,574 --> 00:28:48,041
About a million heart
patients are waiting for me, too.

577
00:28:49,862 --> 00:28:51,795
Right.

578
00:28:51,864 --> 00:28:53,730
You can't let people down.

579
00:28:59,705 --> 00:29:00,871
Hey.

580
00:29:03,575 --> 00:29:05,008
Thanks.

581
00:29:06,245 --> 00:29:07,510
Was it because of the suit?

582
00:29:07,579 --> 00:29:10,391
No. His kidneys failed, and
that caused him to pass out.

583
00:29:10,415 --> 00:29:12,649
But the surgery is going well,

584
00:29:12,718 --> 00:29:14,584
and then we'll get
him on dialysis.

585
00:29:14,653 --> 00:29:19,923
This is just a complication
of Jason's condition.

586
00:29:19,992 --> 00:29:22,993
It's all just complications.

587
00:29:23,062 --> 00:29:25,073
And he should be able to
continue with the study, so...

588
00:29:25,097 --> 00:29:26,263
He won't.

589
00:29:28,500 --> 00:29:30,200
Yeah, this will be his excuse,

590
00:29:30,269 --> 00:29:32,263
and he'll never forgive
me for making him do it.

591
00:29:32,287 --> 00:29:34,922
What? You didn't
make him do this.

592
00:29:34,990 --> 00:29:37,201
He told me once,
we were fighting,

593
00:29:37,225 --> 00:29:39,509
and he told me that
when we woke him

594
00:29:39,578 --> 00:29:42,312
to ask him if he wanted to live,

595
00:29:42,381 --> 00:29:45,865
he only said yes because
he was looking at me,

596
00:29:45,934 --> 00:29:48,835
that if it had been up to him,

597
00:29:48,904 --> 00:29:51,171
if I wasn't there,

598
00:29:51,240 --> 00:29:53,406
he would have said no.

599
00:29:55,560 --> 00:29:56,993
So all this is because of me.

600
00:29:57,062 --> 00:29:58,706
I mean, he's miserable
every day because of me.

601
00:29:58,730 --> 00:30:00,864
And I'm not a wife anymore.

602
00:30:00,916 --> 00:30:03,817
I'm a nursemaid and
a cook and an orderly,

603
00:30:03,886 --> 00:30:05,963
and I never go
home from that work.

604
00:30:05,987 --> 00:30:09,489
I am that work. That's
all I am anymore.

605
00:30:15,063 --> 00:30:16,613
I wanted to have a child.

606
00:30:20,769 --> 00:30:23,253
And I will never,
ever have a child.

607
00:30:26,125 --> 00:30:28,192
I'm sorry.

608
00:30:28,260 --> 00:30:29,938
I'm being selfish and horrible.

609
00:30:29,962 --> 00:30:32,412
No, you're not. No,
no, no. Not at all.

610
00:30:32,480 --> 00:30:34,431
Not at all. I
totally understand.

611
00:30:46,411 --> 00:30:48,211
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

612
00:30:48,280 --> 00:30:50,080
No. It's okay.

613
00:30:51,150 --> 00:30:54,017
<i>Get on out!</i>

614
00:30:54,086 --> 00:30:56,687
<i>Okay, now, that is
a healthy heart sip</i>

615
00:30:56,755 --> 00:30:59,455
<i>that's both delicious
and nutritious.</i>

616
00:30:59,524 --> 00:31:01,725
<i>Thank you very much for that.</i>

617
00:31:01,794 --> 00:31:06,596
<i>Next up, I'm going
to debunk the top five</i>

618
00:31:06,665 --> 00:31:10,266
<i>biggest health myths for you
folks, coming up right after this.</i>

619
00:31:10,335 --> 00:31:13,469
She better include my
suggestion on too much calcium

620
00:31:13,538 --> 00:31:16,339
increasing your
risk of heart disease.

621
00:31:16,408 --> 00:31:18,775
People pop those
pills like candy.

622
00:31:22,181 --> 00:31:23,892
I haven't seen you in two days.

623
00:31:23,916 --> 00:31:25,756
Yeah, I took a couple
extra night shifts.

624
00:31:25,784 --> 00:31:27,495
I went by the
trailer this morning.

625
00:31:27,519 --> 00:31:30,120
Yeah, I just crashed
in the on-call room.

626
00:31:35,660 --> 00:31:37,077
Is something going on?

627
00:31:45,254 --> 00:31:48,538
I need more, Cristina. You know?

628
00:31:48,607 --> 00:31:51,308
I just can't keep...

629
00:31:51,377 --> 00:31:53,043
I just need more, you know.

630
00:31:53,112 --> 00:31:56,196
More from you, more from us.

631
00:31:56,264 --> 00:31:58,424
- Another, please?
- You got it!

632
00:31:58,967 --> 00:32:00,478
Okay, let's just
get out of here.

633
00:32:00,502 --> 00:32:01,646
Nope.

634
00:32:01,670 --> 00:32:03,214
Let's go home.
Just sleep this off,

635
00:32:03,238 --> 00:32:04,732
and let's talk about it
in the morning, can we...

636
00:32:04,756 --> 00:32:06,996
We don't have a home, Cristina.

637
00:32:07,059 --> 00:32:09,943
I have a trailer, and you
have a room at Karev's house.

638
00:32:10,012 --> 00:32:11,511
It's not...

639
00:32:14,049 --> 00:32:15,126
Another, please.

640
00:32:15,150 --> 00:32:16,216
Right up!

641
00:32:27,829 --> 00:32:29,949
There you go. Thank you.

642
00:32:30,399 --> 00:32:32,665
There's too many.

643
00:32:32,734 --> 00:32:34,334
The kids outnumber the adults.

644
00:32:34,403 --> 00:32:36,903
Should've thought of that
before we adopted again.

645
00:32:36,971 --> 00:32:39,817
I mean, what if there's a
mutiny? Derek and I will lose.

646
00:32:39,841 --> 00:32:42,509
Well, not until the
third one can walk.

647
00:32:43,811 --> 00:32:45,811
So, you broke up again?

648
00:32:48,850 --> 00:32:52,352
Same thing, over and over.

649
00:32:55,590 --> 00:32:59,125
You know what else is the same?

650
00:32:59,194 --> 00:33:01,827
This.

651
00:33:01,896 --> 00:33:06,199
You and I laying in this bed,
talking about you and Owen.

652
00:33:06,268 --> 00:33:08,768
Why do you keep
doing this to yourself?

653
00:33:12,741 --> 00:33:14,240
I need help.

654
00:33:19,013 --> 00:33:20,296
Mer, you have to help me.

655
00:33:21,766 --> 00:33:23,349
Don't let me go back to him,

656
00:33:23,418 --> 00:33:26,085
for his good and mine.

657
00:33:26,655 --> 00:33:28,271
Please help me.

658
00:33:28,340 --> 00:33:31,508
Of course. Of
course I'll help you.

659
00:33:37,632 --> 00:33:39,744
What do you mean? It's been six
months since my last procedure!

660
00:33:39,768 --> 00:33:41,000
Your hand's still not healed!

661
00:33:41,069 --> 00:33:44,037
You need more PT and
more time in the skills lab.

662
00:33:44,105 --> 00:33:45,705
You are not
stepping into that OR,

663
00:33:45,774 --> 00:33:47,474
not today, maybe not ever!

664
00:33:47,543 --> 00:33:49,103
All right, first of all, you
need to lower your voice.

665
00:33:49,127 --> 00:33:51,227
Okay, so what,
nobody can yell at you?

666
00:33:51,296 --> 00:33:53,274
Why's that? Why is that?
Because you're an Avery?

667
00:33:53,298 --> 00:33:54,759
That has nothing to do
with any of this, and you...

668
00:33:54,783 --> 00:33:57,383
Some pampered little rich
boy who was gifted a hospital,

669
00:33:57,453 --> 00:34:01,054
so he thinks that it's okay to
go ahead and endanger patients,

670
00:34:01,122 --> 00:34:04,006
'cause he's too damn proud to
admit that he can't operate anymore!

671
00:34:04,076 --> 00:34:05,125
Dr. Hunt!

672
00:34:15,954 --> 00:34:17,532
Do you know how many infants

673
00:34:17,556 --> 00:34:19,534
are born without a
pulmonary artery?

674
00:34:19,558 --> 00:34:20,823
Cristina, I'm so sorry.

675
00:34:20,892 --> 00:34:22,570
But there is a
surgery to correct it.

676
00:34:22,594 --> 00:34:24,160
It's called unifocalization,

677
00:34:24,229 --> 00:34:26,374
which I was doing with a robot.

678
00:34:26,398 --> 00:34:27,638
But now Shane is finishing it

679
00:34:27,682 --> 00:34:29,660
because you paged me
"911" like a million times.

680
00:34:29,684 --> 00:34:30,861
So whatever it
is, it better be...

681
00:34:30,885 --> 00:34:31,968
It's Owen.

682
00:34:33,388 --> 00:34:35,483
He wanted to work a shift.
I didn't feel comfortable.

683
00:34:35,507 --> 00:34:37,590
He only agreed to get
in a bed if I paged you.

684
00:34:39,361 --> 00:34:40,477
You came.

685
00:34:42,764 --> 00:34:44,004
Give us a minute.

686
00:34:52,006 --> 00:34:53,951
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

687
00:34:53,975 --> 00:34:55,815
Oh, God, you stink.

688
00:34:57,846 --> 00:34:59,529
You tried to start a shift?

689
00:34:59,598 --> 00:35:01,965
Are you insane? You
could've hurt someone.

690
00:35:02,033 --> 00:35:04,301
Yeah. Yeah. I love you.

691
00:35:07,622 --> 00:35:09,523
This has got to
stop. I love you.

692
00:35:09,591 --> 00:35:12,859
I love you. I love you,

693
00:35:12,928 --> 00:35:15,529
and I see you every day,

694
00:35:15,597 --> 00:35:17,637
and I can't have you.

695
00:35:19,517 --> 00:35:21,550
So how am I supposed
to keep doing this,

696
00:35:21,619 --> 00:35:24,470
keep working here,

697
00:35:24,539 --> 00:35:27,040
when every time I turn around,

698
00:35:29,510 --> 00:35:30,577
I see your face?

699
00:35:31,163 --> 00:35:32,562
Owen...

700
00:35:34,099 --> 00:35:36,115
Owen, Owen, Owen, Owen...

701
00:35:36,184 --> 00:35:41,037
I love you. Please. Please.
Please marry me. Just marry me.

702
00:35:41,106 --> 00:35:43,573
Owen... Why can't
you just marry me?

703
00:35:43,642 --> 00:35:45,758
Please, I'm begging
you. I'm begging.

704
00:35:45,844 --> 00:35:47,344
I am begging you.

705
00:35:47,412 --> 00:35:49,223
I mean, we should
never have called it quits.

706
00:35:49,247 --> 00:35:52,515
We should never have called
it quits when we did. Please.

707
00:36:01,026 --> 00:36:02,258
Please marry me.

708
00:36:13,805 --> 00:36:15,705
Well, there's no
sign of him yet,

709
00:36:15,774 --> 00:36:17,084
but there's still
plenty of time,

710
00:36:17,108 --> 00:36:18,542
so there's no reason to panic.

711
00:36:18,610 --> 00:36:20,037
I'm not panicked. Okay.

712
00:36:20,061 --> 00:36:21,995
Can you get my belt? Sure.

713
00:36:26,835 --> 00:36:28,367
You look beautiful.

714
00:36:28,436 --> 00:36:29,936
Thanks.

715
00:36:30,005 --> 00:36:32,889
He is late. How could
he be late to this?

716
00:36:32,957 --> 00:36:34,957
I'll go look for him again.

717
00:36:41,649 --> 00:36:43,161
Okay, we've got a
full house, people.

718
00:36:43,185 --> 00:36:44,684
Page anyone who's available.

719
00:36:44,752 --> 00:36:46,819
10-Year-old female,
thrown from a vehicle,

720
00:36:46,888 --> 00:36:49,672
multiple blunt injuries
and hypotensive.

721
00:36:49,741 --> 00:36:52,392
Hey, you, assess her, then
rush her up to radiology,

722
00:36:52,461 --> 00:36:54,160
get a CT with contrast.

723
00:36:54,229 --> 00:36:55,740
Then page me as
soon as... Excuse me.

724
00:36:55,764 --> 00:36:57,329
Contrast, like the iodine dye?

725
00:36:57,398 --> 00:36:59,878
I'm allergic to that. Do you
think my daughter could be, too?

726
00:36:59,934 --> 00:37:02,819
We'll run a test and check.
Not a problem. Excuse me.

727
00:37:03,471 --> 00:37:04,704
What've you got?

728
00:37:10,862 --> 00:37:12,973
Do you want me
to call him again?

729
00:37:12,997 --> 00:37:14,113
No.

730
00:37:28,046 --> 00:37:30,814
Do you have to take
that? 'Cause you can go.

731
00:37:30,882 --> 00:37:33,817
It's not like you haven't been
through this with me before.

732
00:37:33,885 --> 00:37:37,420
It's a general page,
for whoever's on call.

733
00:37:37,489 --> 00:37:40,055
I'm not even on call.
I'm not going anywhere.

734
00:37:45,280 --> 00:37:46,423
What happened?

735
00:37:46,447 --> 00:37:48,042
She was seizing,
severe allergic reaction.

736
00:37:48,066 --> 00:37:50,344
I was passing by and
saw this intern freaking out.

737
00:37:50,368 --> 00:37:52,435
I've given her a .3 EPI.

738
00:37:52,503 --> 00:37:53,853
Well, did anyone order contrast?

739
00:37:53,922 --> 00:37:55,122
Was she tested for allergies?

740
00:37:55,173 --> 00:37:56,606
I got paged. What's going on?

741
00:37:56,675 --> 00:37:58,491
We need to get her
to the OR immediately.

742
00:37:58,560 --> 00:38:01,311
Let's start her on
Benadryl and steroids, stat!

743
00:38:01,379 --> 00:38:03,491
Is this your patient? Yes.

744
00:38:03,515 --> 00:38:05,359
Why didn't you screen her
for any contrast allergies?

745
00:38:05,383 --> 00:38:06,660
I did. It's not here.

746
00:38:06,684 --> 00:38:07,895
I mean, there's no
record of any tests.

747
00:38:07,919 --> 00:38:08,980
I ordered it. You did?

748
00:38:09,004 --> 00:38:10,581
Yes! Yes. You sure? You did?

749
00:38:10,605 --> 00:38:11,854
I ordered the damn test!

750
00:38:13,558 --> 00:38:14,598
Didn't I?

751
00:38:19,414 --> 00:38:21,225
Cutting it a little
close, don't you think?

752
00:38:21,249 --> 00:38:22,982
Hi. Sorry I'm late. I know.

753
00:38:23,051 --> 00:38:24,662
I got held up, and
there was traffic and...

754
00:38:24,686 --> 00:38:26,953
Anyway, sorry. I'm here now.

755
00:38:27,022 --> 00:38:29,038
You look incredible.

756
00:38:30,975 --> 00:38:32,015
Thank you.

757
00:38:32,727 --> 00:38:34,894
Well, shall we do this?

758
00:38:36,247 --> 00:38:37,646
Let's.

759
00:38:42,053 --> 00:38:43,920
This is unacceptable.

760
00:38:43,989 --> 00:38:45,500
Things like this keep happening,

761
00:38:45,524 --> 00:38:46,934
and this time there
was a kid involved.

762
00:38:46,958 --> 00:38:49,358
And I'm not looking the
other way any longer.

763
00:38:49,427 --> 00:38:51,338
He's unreliable, a
danger to his patients.

764
00:38:51,362 --> 00:38:52,695
I mean...

765
00:38:52,763 --> 00:38:57,200
Did you smell his breath?

766
00:38:57,268 --> 00:38:59,229
Yeah, well, let's just wait
for the breathalyzer results.

767
00:38:59,253 --> 00:39:02,354
No. We need to convene
an emergency board meeting.

768
00:39:02,424 --> 00:39:04,757
Right now, Derek. Right now.

769
00:39:04,826 --> 00:39:07,026
She's a pioneer, an inspiration,

770
00:39:07,095 --> 00:39:09,228
a mentor, and, I'm proud to say,

771
00:39:09,297 --> 00:39:12,464
my friend for over 15 years.

772
00:39:12,533 --> 00:39:13,800
Please welcome,

773
00:39:13,868 --> 00:39:16,046
for an unprecedented
fourth consecutive year,

774
00:39:16,070 --> 00:39:18,404
tonight's Harper
Avery Award recipient,

775
00:39:18,472 --> 00:39:19,689
Dr. Cristina Yang.

776
00:39:24,830 --> 00:39:26,779
<i>I came as soon as I could.</i>

777
00:39:26,848 --> 00:39:28,915
You know he's just
sitting out there waiting?

778
00:39:28,984 --> 00:39:30,661
April, you run the
trauma department.

779
00:39:30,685 --> 00:39:32,563
You work with him more
closely than anybody else.

780
00:39:32,587 --> 00:39:35,354
Do you trust Owen
Hunt to treat patients?

781
00:39:36,557 --> 00:39:38,057
He is my mentor,

782
00:39:38,126 --> 00:39:39,558
and he trained me.

783
00:39:39,628 --> 00:39:42,528
We value your opinion,
April. That's why you're here.

784
00:39:42,597 --> 00:39:44,797
Just be honest.

785
00:39:44,866 --> 00:39:47,033
Do you trust the man?

786
00:39:58,046 --> 00:40:01,014
No, I don't.

787
00:40:01,082 --> 00:40:03,866
I move to terminate him,
effective immediately.

788
00:40:03,935 --> 00:40:06,619
If there's one thing I've
learned over the years,

789
00:40:06,688 --> 00:40:11,724
it's that it only takes one
person, one patient, one moment,

790
00:40:11,793 --> 00:40:14,460
to change your life forever.

791
00:40:14,529 --> 00:40:18,965
To change your perspective,
color your thinking,

792
00:40:19,033 --> 00:40:23,636
to force you to re-evaluate
everything you think you know.

793
00:40:23,705 --> 00:40:27,623
<i>To make you ask yourself
the toughest questions.</i>

794
00:40:29,160 --> 00:40:30,727
Do you know who you are?

795
00:40:32,530 --> 00:40:35,648
<i>Do you understand what
has happened to you?</i>

796
00:40:36,784 --> 00:40:39,018
Do you want to live this way?

797
00:40:42,807 --> 00:40:45,687
<i>I'm sorry, but I have
to ask one more time.</i>

798
00:40:46,578 --> 00:40:49,011
Jason,

799
00:40:49,080 --> 00:40:51,447
would you like me
to remove the vent?

800
00:41:08,833 --> 00:41:10,833
Okay.

801
00:41:51,643 --> 00:41:52,643
Hey, watch your hand.

802
00:41:53,762 --> 00:41:54,844
Thanks.

803
00:41:54,912 --> 00:41:55,912
No problem.

804
00:42:00,668 --> 00:42:02,830
Hey, Cristina.
Hey. You got a sec?

805
00:42:02,854 --> 00:42:04,448
I could use a set of
eyes on my patient.

806
00:42:04,472 --> 00:42:05,905
Yeah. Just give me one...

807
00:42:10,744 --> 00:42:12,478
Never mind. What do you got?
